  "local_port": 36330,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Reliance JIO uses a technology called VoLTE (Voice over LTE) for its voice calls. VoLTE allows voice calls to be made over the 4G LTE network. While VoLTE itself doesn't require an internet connection in the traditional sense (like data usage), it does need the 4G network to be active.\n\nHere are a few points to clarify:\n\n1. **VoLTE Calls:** When you make a voice call using JIO, it uses the 4G network. This does not consume your data pack, so in that sense, an \"internet connection\" (data usage) is not required.\n\n2. **Data Usage:** If you use JIO apps like JIOChat or WhatsApp for voice calls, then yes, you'll need an active internet connection (data plan), and it will consume data from your plan.\n\n3. **Fallback:** In areas where 4G coverage is poor, JIO might use 2G/3G networks for calls, but this is less common as JIO primarily operates on 4G.\n\nIn summary, for standard voice calls on Reliance JIO using VoLTE, you don't need an internet connection in terms of data usage, but you do need to be connected to the 4G network.",
